 vague &quot;years ago&quot;) an adult human male, who was showing off to his friends his great physical prowess, snuck into the Kabul Zoo and into Marjan's pen to wrestle the lion. Marjan, probably thinking himself under attack, killed the idiot. The next day the idiot's brother or his cousin (again reports are not clear) returned to the zoo and tossed a hand grenade at Marjan. Marjan was blinded in both eyes and crippled.<br><br>Unfortunately, Marjan wasn't the only abused animal there. An elephant, the only one at the zoo, was used for target practice by a so-called &quot;soldier of god&quot; wielding a grenade launcher. The elephant was killed. There is a bear there, the local male adults and male children thought it amusing to wave food at her, which she would reach through the bars for. When she did, they'd whack her with sticks and poles. So many of them were abused, for entertainment. Some were simply killed and eaten out of hunger, which may be understandable, but torture is not.<br><br>Marjan died not long after international animal welfare/protection groups arrived to help.<br><br>I've posted about Marjan's death on a number of boards, and likely by morning I'm going to be inundated with messages from people wondering why, with all else that's going on, am I crying over an animal in Afghanistan? I'm crying because it's sad. People mistreat each other all of the time, but if we are going to consider ourselves superior to all life on Earth, it's time we started trying to act like it and stop mistreating those that many humans consider &quot;inferior.&quot;<br><br>It's also interesting to note, that with the recent international media coverage in the Kabul area (and non-Taliban troops present), there is suddenly a large number of locals who are concerned about the animals.<br><br>Rest in Peace, Noble Marjan, King of Beasts<br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.wspa-international.org/news/images/afghan2-2.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>If you'd like to help, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.wspa-international.org">www.wspa-international.org</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>Karuna<br><br> <p>Is insanity in the observed, or in the observer?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/upsylent1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Psylent1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/12/02 5:43:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://jawjrfotofile.homestead.com/files/deathdealer1.jpg height=85 width=85></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Greatest Mystery of All</span><hr size=1> I have made several posts on different boards concerning the plight of the Kabul Zoo myself as well...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/emoticons_classic/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Thanks for that link; it looks like some relief is fanally coming in to help improve the conditions there. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/emoticons_classic/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/udotzap.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DOTZAP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Angelight</span><br>  