hide the tusks if they are there. They will drag them in opposite directions and hide them. Why? Because they know that they are hunted for their tusks and are trying in their own small way to fight against it. I think that is amazing, and just shows that animals are not dumb beasts. Humans are.  <p><html><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/geofon/frog.gif"></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/udavidrichmond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>David Richmond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/2/02 6:25:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Greatest Mystery of All</span><hr size=1> If goodness exists in some potent form, there must be some reason for evil, we are unaware of.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ufraterliber.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FraterLiber</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/2/02 8:27:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm35.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Greatest Mystery of All</span><hr size=1> Each of us is capable of both extremes.   Each of us is capable of the worst evil and the highest good that a human being can achieve.  <br><br>Some of us do more good, others more harm, but all of us do both, and the horrible part is, it can be almost impossible to tell which is which.  That's why they say the road to hell is paved with good intentions.  You think you're